CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1967, pg. 15, reads: "ULG Boat Ride - For the past few years, one of the social highlights of the season has been a boat ride sponsored by the Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh. This year was no exception and a happy throng was on hand for the event held recently.  Among Guild members who spearheaded the affair were those in first picture.  From left they are: Mmes. Arlene Palamore, Margaretta Burton, Helen Chalfont, chairman; Mary Alexander, president, and Juanita McCarter...- All Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Arlene Palamore, Margaretta Burton, Helen Chalfont, Mary Alexander, and Juanita McCarter, gathered around table exchanging documents, on riverboat for Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh's annual boat ride
